com.defano.jmonet.tools.util

Class MarchingAnts

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.defano.jmonet.tools.util.MarchingAnts

  • public class MarchingAnts
extends Object
    A class for animating a dashed border stroke ("marching ants") commonly found in selection tools. This singleton class manages the ant animation by instantiating a single-threaded scheduled executor. Multiple "ants" paths can be drawn with this singleton by registering multiple listeners.

      • getAnimationPeriodMs

        public int getAnimationPeriodMs()
        Gets the period of the ants animation, in milliseconds. That is, the number of milliseconds delayed before redrawing the position of the ants. Lower values means faster moving ants.
        Returns:
        The period of the ants animation, in milliseconds.

      • getAntWidth

        public int getAntWidth()
        Gets the width of each ant, in pixels. Note that when stroking a selection outline with marching ants, the ants are centered on the selected shape. Therefore, wide ants will partially obscure the selection being made.
        Returns:
        The width of each ant, in pixels.
